						               													<description>Based on a classical weapon dated as early as the 12th century, this is the Cannon Indeed!, an easy-to-pick-up Card Game based on Math, Luck and Logic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cannon Indeed! is specially designed for Single Player only. &amp;#10;However, Multiplayer Mode is supported with the involvement of multiple decks (up to 4 players). There are 2 multiplayer modes &amp;ndash; PvP and Coop.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For Single Player mode, the goal is to destroy all enemy CANNONs in play. However, you will lose if your TOWER deck has ZERO card. For each CANNON damage dealt is in the form of putting the top card of the TOWER deck into discard pile. Each CANNON will deal damage based on the total number of AMMOs sharing the same colour as the CANNON. There are 4 different colours based on CMYK Colour and Black(K)can represent any colour.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game, the Player will go through 3 phases. &amp;#10;First is the Player's phase whereby he or she is given 3 actions to either: &amp;#10;A) Draw 1 card from TOWER deck &amp;#10;B) Put 1 card from hand into play &amp;#10;C) Discard 2 identical cards from hand to destroy target enemy AMMO. &amp;#10;Player can repeat the same action as long as 3 actions are fulfilled.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Second is the Special Event Phase whereby he or she will roll a 6-sided dice to determine one of the Special event to occur.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Third is the Enemy Phase whereby the Player will count and receive the total number of damage dealt by all the CANNONs in play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Player repeats each phase for multiple rounds until all the enemy CANNONs in play are destroyed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
